                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/452</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-19T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Bethlehem Steel Company advise Department of report from its manager that
                    anti-American feeling very strong among rebels, that the mines are practically
                    without adequate protection as marines are kept constantly moving and that Cuban
                    Government cannot end trouble without substantial assistance.</p>
                <p>You will communicate this information to President Menocal and ascertain why
                    ample and permanent protection is not furnished these properties. Report by
                    cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
